abstract: China Merchants Holdings International signed an agreement on Friday to form a $911 million joint venture to merge its port facilities in China’s Qingdao Port with those of its partners, including Cosco Pacific and A.P. Moller Maersk.
snippet: China Merchants Holdings International signed an agreement on Friday to form a $911 million joint venture to merge its port facilities in China’s Qingdao Port with those of its partners, including Cosco Pacific and A.P. Moller Maersk.
lead_paragraph: China Merchants Holdings International signed an agreement on Friday to form a $911 million joint venture to merge its port facilities in China’s Qingdao Port with those of its partners, including Cosco Pacific and A.P. Moller Maersk, Reuters reported.

headline.main: Chinese Port Operator Strikes Deal in Qingdao

abstract: The flying monks of Shaolin may soon learn how to float, as well. The holding company set to run the tourism-related assets of the Shaolin Temple may go public next year.
